main event: A bright light was observed in the sky by a Coast Guard ship on November 29, 1964, for a duration of about 30 minutes.
interesting points: The object was reported to be moving for 1 to 2 minutes before disappearing., The sighting occurred at coordinates 34.20N 163.48E in the Pacific., No physical evidence was found related to the sighting., The report suggested that the object was unlikely to be an atmospheric phenomenon or celestial body., The angle of elevation of the object was at 25 degrees.
witness description: observed from a Coast Guard ship
